Patch Set 5:

> > (1 comment)
 > >
 > > thanks for taking this up.
 > 
 > we can't use is_uuid_like method there because this method is just
 > to validate a UUID but there uuid.UUID(image['id']) function is
 > generating a uuid based on the provided parameter (image['id']).

Hi Sudhir,

Also you can definitely use uuidutils.is_uuid_like(image['id']) here, it will not create any problem.

What actually happening now is you are creating a new uuid object by passing existing image-id where as is_uuid_like method will check existing image_id is valid uuid or not. So its safe to use is_uuid_like method and remove import uuid line.
